videos.description: Stanford's Hannah Jump drains a 3-point shot from way downtown against South Carolina.
videos.headline: Hannah Jump drills NBA range 3-pointer for Stanford

videos.description: Brea Beal's persistence pays off for South Carolina after her offensive rebound leads to an and-1.
videos.headline: Brea Beal collects her own rebound and drains and-1

videos.description: Lacie Hull extends Stanford's lead with an outrageous 3-pointer from long range.
videos.headline: Lacie Hull beats the shot clock with circus-shot 3

videos.description: Haley Jones gets the easy basket after a perfectly executed backdoor cut.
videos.headline: Anna Wilson feeds Haley Jones for the lay-in on the backdoor cut

videos.description: Destanni Henderson makes a great pass for a bucket and then comes up with a steal leading to a basket.
videos.headline: Destanni Henderson sets up back-to-back buckets for South Carolina

videos.description: Aliyah Boston puts South Carolina ahead for good with just over a minute to play.
videos.headline: Aliyah Boston hits the go-ahead bucket for South Carolina

videos.description: No. 1 South Carolina uses a 10-0 run in the third quarter and some clutch buckets in the fourth to keep its perfect record intact.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (South Carolina comes back from 17-point deficit to beat Stanford) 2021/12/21 ESHEET

videos.headline: South Carolina comes back from 18-point deficit to beat Stanford

videos.description: Following the 65-61 win over No. 2 Stanford, No. 1 South Carolina's Destanni Henderson explains how the Gamecocks sparked the largest comeback in school history.
videos.headline: Discipline, defense leads Gamecocks' 18-point comeback
